From: ROCKNIX Layer 14 cemu flake
Subject: [PATCH] ScreenSaver::SetInhibit no-op on Linux

nixpkgs SDL2 is sdl2-compat (a SDL3 shim). SDL3's video-subsystem
initialization path invokes std::regex code that segfaults on aarch64
during cemu's first ScreenSaver::SetInhibit(true) call (which happens
on every ROM load).

Cemu already has a #if BOOST_OS_MACOS bypass for the same crash on
macOS. We add #if BOOST_OS_LINUX since we observe the identical
crash signature on Linux/aarch64 with sdl2-compat.

Cost of the bypass: cemu does not inhibit the screensaver while a
game is running. In our Layer 14 sway-kiosk profile there is no
screensaver running anyway, and any future inhibition would be
handled at the sway layer.

--- a/src/util/ScreenSaver/ScreenSaver.h
+++ b/src/util/ScreenSaver/ScreenSaver.h
@@ -6,9 +6,12 @@ class ScreenSaver
 public:
   static void SetInhibit(bool inhibit)
   {
-	  // temporary workaround because feature crashes on macOS
+    // temporary workaround because feature crashes on macOS
 #if BOOST_OS_MACOS
-	  return;
+    return;
+#endif
+#if BOOST_OS_LINUX
+    return;
 #endif
     // Initialize video subsystem if necessary
     if (SDL_WasInit(SDL_INIT_VIDEO) == 0)
